        <h1>What I made last night</h1>
        <h3>Kale Salad</h3>
          <ul class="recipe">
            <li>one bunch of kale</li>
            <li>juice of one lemon</li>
            <li>parmesan cheese</li>
            <li>olive oil</li>
            <li>salt and pepper</li>
          </ul>

          <ol class="recipe">
            <li>Wash kale to your standards. I take the extra time to inspect each leaf to make sure I don't end up eating any aphids. But that's a personal preference.</li>
            <li>With or without aphids, chop kale into bite-sized pieces. Massage your kale if you'd like.</li>
            <li>Whisk lemon juice, salt and pepper together and then drizzle in olive oil.</li>
            <li>Pour dressing and shredded parmesan over kale, mix and devour.</li>
          </ol>

          <img class="food-pics" src="http://www.gimmesomeoven.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/lemon-parmesan-kale-salad.jpg" alt="Kale Salad" />
      </div>

